This paper discusses the technical methods used by China to block access to the Tor anonymity network, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the impact of this censorship on network infrastructure (cs.NI), as well as the political and social implications of censorship (cs.CY). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of software and network protocols (cs.SE) to circumvent censorship, and the potential for future research in this area (cs.DC).
